===Etymology===
From Chinese [[古琴]] (gǔqín), from [[古]] ‘ancient’ + [[琴]] ‘stringed instrument’.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|guqin|guqin}}
# A plucked seven-string Chinese [[musical instrument]] of the [[zither]] family 
#:*'''1982''': Among those who will be making the Otter valley resound to the strains of the ''guzheng'' and ''erhu'' is Wu Weng-wang, who plays a piece of music 1,800 years old on the '''''guqin''''', an instrument known to have existed 3,000 years ago — ''The Times'', 25 May 1982, p.10 col. C

